{"id": 243368952, "title": "5 Army jawans die as T-72 sinks in gushing river near LAC in Ladakh", "text": "Srinagar: Five Indian soldiers including a Junior Commissioned Office (JCO) drowned to death after they were swept away while crossing a gushing river in a T-72 tank in the Nyoma-Chushul area close to the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in eastern Ladakh early Saturday.Reports reaching Leh said that the mishap occurred near Mandir Morh, 148-km from Ladakh\u2019s main town, at 3 am and that the bodies of the soldiers have been recovered.The Army jawans were reportedly on a training mission and chose to cross the river which was in spate following heavy rains in the region in a tank. The reports said that the tank, however, sank in the impact of flash floods and with it all those on board were drowned to death.", "summary": "", "url": "https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/5-army-jawans-die-as-t-72-sinks-in-gushing-river-near-lac-in-ladakh-1308624", "image": "https://www.deccanchronicle.com/h-upload/2024/06/29/1100373-tanker.webp", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 06:48:42", "author": "DC Correspondent", "authors": ["DC Correspondent"], "language": "en", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": 0.101}